@startuml
title Figure 1. High-Level RideNow Architecture

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
}
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor white
  BorderColor black
  FontColor black
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor white
  BorderColor black
}

actor "Client App" as Client

component "Broker Node" as Broker
component "Notification Node" as Notification
component "Driver Node" as Driver
component "Route Node" as Route
component "Pricing Node" as Pricing
component "Payment Node" as Payment
component "Tracking Node" as Tracking

Client --> Broker : request / status

Broker --> Notification : publish intents / events

Notification --> Driver : assignment / availability events
Notification --> Route : route / ETA requests
Notification --> Pricing : pricing requests
Notification --> Payment : payment requests
Notification --> Tracking : trip state requests

Driver --> Notification : location / availability updates
Route --> Notification : route / ETA outcomes
Pricing --> Notification : fare outcomes
Payment --> Notification : payment outcomes
Tracking --> Notification : trip status updates

Notification --> Broker : downstream outcomes
Broker --> Client : feedback / status

note bottom of Notification
Central asynchronous dissemination node
for intents, updates, and service outcomes
end note

note bottom of Broker
Single customer-facing coordination service
end note

@enduml
